  "body": "### Description\n\nThe current implementation of `eth_estimateGas` must be modified (add a field to the CallParameter object). This new field will allow to choose whether you want an estimate with strict checks or not (nonce, balance account, etc.)\n\n- The current implementation behavior : \n\nConsidering an account with 0 ETH If we are sending a transaction with the value == 0 wei the API return an estimate. If the value is > 0 wei the API return an error of type `Upfront cost exceeds account balance`\n\n**Script used to test the API behavior** on goerli : \n\n```\n    var transaction = {\n      from: \"0x97Bd0630482F1A146C47450685BA7CEBe120213e\",\n      to: \"0x22d491Bde2303f2f43325b2108D26f1eAbA1e32b\",\n      value: 0,\n      gas: 1000000,\n      gasPrice: 9000000000\n    };\nâ€‹\n    // Estimate the gas cost for the transaction on goerli\n    provider.estimateGas(transaction).then((gas) => {\n        console.log(gas); // if value = 0 BigNumber { _hex: '0x5208' }\n    }).catch((e) => {  \n        console.log(e);\n    });\n```\n\nThe default value of this new field should be \"false\". So no strict control by default. We should enumerate what checks we add when strict:true is set\n\n***Note :*** this would also impact `eth_call`  as it uses the same call parameter object.\n\n",
